                type="document" xml:id="d104">
                <head>104. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss> Administrator <persName corresp="#p_BDE1"
                        >David E. Bell</persName> visited Paris February 21–23, Bonn February 23–24,
                    and London, February 24–27, 1965, to discuss possible strategies for the
                    improvement of the coordination of U.S. and European worldwide economic aid
                    programs. Documentation on <persName corresp="#p_BDE1">Bell</persName>’s trip is
                    in the Washington National Records Center, RG 286, <gloss target="#t_DAC1"
                        >DAC</gloss> Material: FRC 70 <gloss target="#t_A1">A</gloss> 5922;
                    Trip—Administrator <persName corresp="#p_BDE1">David Bell</persName>, Paris,
                    Bonn, London, February 21–27, 1965. For <persName corresp="#p_BDE1"
                        >Bell</persName>’s report on his trip and <gloss target="#t_AID1"
                        >AID</gloss> senior level discussion about it, see <ref target="#d105"
                        >Documents 105</ref> and <ref target="#d106">106</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
